"I've had it for the last week. It probably comes from the soft beds they  have in Europe," he said. "I could not go full out for the five sets."
But the Chinese American paid tribute to the mental strength demonstrated  by his opponent.
"You're always going to have aches and pains in tennis and I don't to take  anything away from Jaime.
"I thought he was tired in the fourth set but he got it back in the fifth.  He was able to play me wide with his forehand and I should have come in far  more and attacked."
